<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1435,1786]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Remarks.— 
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[286,415,1435,1462]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 276" refId="ref70911" refString="Stal, C. (1866) Hemiptera Homoptera Latr. Hemiptera Africana, 4, 1 - 276, pl. 1." type="journal article" year="1866">Stål (1866)</bibRefCitation>
described the characteristic features for what was a subgenus as a head wider than the mesonotum, eyes large, about half the width of the head, well separated from the ocelli, postclypeus swollen with central sulcus, the anterior somewhat prominent, prothorax without larteral part of pronotal collar, very obtuse angle formed on anterior of convex pronotal collar lateral angle, fore wing ulnar cells about as wide at base as apically, fore femora with three spines and small apical spine, carina formed on male tergite 
<quantity box="[1069,1111,1580,1606]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
timbal cavity, timbals angled obliquely posteriorly, opercula curved mediad, meracanthus large, triangular, abdominal segments narrowing posteriorly, large dorsal beak on pygofer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1435,1786]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Distribution.—The genus has been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[756,891,1688,1714]" name="Madagascar" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and much of Asia and one species reported from South America (although this is probably a mistake) (
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf, Z. P." box="[745,914,1723,1750]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 492" refId="ref69874" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 b) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 2. Tibicinidae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1564, i-vi + 1 - 492." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Duffels, J. P. &amp; van der Laan, P. A." box="[924,1253,1723,1750]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref68709" refString="Duffels, J. P. &amp; van der Laan, P. A. (1985) Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Homoptera, Auchenorhyncha) 1956 - 1980. Series Entomologica 34. Dr. W. Junk Publishers, Dordrect, 414 pp." type="book" year="1985">Duffels &amp; van der Laan 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[1264,1425,1724,1750]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref70566" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2013) Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea). With contributions to the bibliography by Martin H. Villet. Elsevier / Academic Press, San Diego, 1001 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / b 978 - 0 - 12 - 416647 - 9.00001 - 2" type="book" year="2013">Sanborn 2013</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Duffels, J. P." box="[151,315,1760,1786]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="77 - 104" refId="ref68651" refString="Duffels, J. P. (2011) New genera and species of the tribe Taphurini (Hemiptera, Cicadidae) from Sundaland. Mitteilungen aus dem Museum f ̡ r Naturkunde im Berlin, Deutsche Entomologishe Zeitschrift, 58, 77 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 201100006" type="journal article" year="2011">Duffels (2011)</bibRefCitation>
transferred some species from Sundaland into new related genera.
</paragraph>
